Students line up outside to rehearse their elevator pitches before entering, where they upload resumes at kiosks, compare swag items, and receive assistance from career counselors on suitable industries and networking etiquette. Representatives from nonprofits emphasize mission-driven career paths, while alumni volunteers provide motivational talks and an engineering society sponsors a resume review table. As the event concludes, students exit with tote bags, business cards, and internship application QR codes, discussing their experiences in the quad, and the dean thanks recruiters for their support.
